-- Turkey's Garanti applies to issue bonds worth 700 mln lira
-- By Ece Toksabay
-- Fri Jul 11, 2014 10:45AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, July 11 (Reuters) - Turkish lender Garanti applied to the Capital Markets Board to issue bonds worth 700 million lira ($330 million), it said on Friday.

The bank made the statement to Istanbul stock exchange.